<!-- ================= THE GAP ================= -->
<section class="ceo-grey">
  <div class="ceo-wrap ceo-sec">
    <div class="ceo-max720">
      <div class="ceo-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">The vision-to-reality gap</div>
      <h2 class="ceo-h2">You set the plan. Then you hope.</h2>
      <p class="ceo-body" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:44rem;">The strategy lives in a deck. The org lives in a hundred tools and a thousand conversations. Between the two is a gap you can't see across &mdash; and you only find out it widened when a number misses.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ceo-grid3 reveal">
      <div class="ceo-card">
        <span class="ceo-chip" style="background:rgba(220,38,38,.1);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M2 12s3.5-7 10-7 10 7 10 7-3.5 7-10 7S2 12 2 12z"/><path d="M3 3l18 18"/></svg></span>
        <h3>The plan disappears into the org</h3>
        <p>Your three-year targets become a quarterly ritual, not a daily force. Below the leadership team, almost no one can tell you how their work ladders up to the number you actually care about.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ceo-card">
        <span class="ceo-chip" style="background:rgba(217,119,6,.12);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#d97706" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 2l9 5v6c0 5-3.8 8.2-9 9-5.2-.8-9-4-9-9V7z"/></svg></span>
        <h3>It still runs on you</h3>
        <p>You can't fully step back, because you can't fully see &mdash; whether the right people are in the right seats, where the business depends on a single person, what's actually getting done.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ceo-card">
        <span class="ceo-chip" style="background:rgba(13,125,242,.1);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><rect x="5" y="8" width="14" height="11" rx="3"/><path d="M12 4v4M9 13h.01M15 13h.01"/></svg></span>
        <h3>Half your future workforce is invisible</h3>
        <p>Your team is bringing on AI agents that do real work. They're not on the chart, not on the scoreboard, not in the plan &mdash; so you're steering the next decade half-blind.</p>
